data.mission: Add an explicit 'Comprehensive v1 Definition' section (either in /outputs/roadmap_v1.md or a companion scope file) listing included/excluded subtopics, prioritization rules, and required outputs per subtopic (e.g., 1 theorem + 1 canonical example + 2 sources).

Implement a tiny Python skeleton (e.g., /outputs/src/ + one script) that writes deterministic artifacts (run_stamp.json, run.log, and one plot/data file) and add one pytest test verifying those artifacts are created.

Define a fixed output schema (e.g., outputs/results.json fields + figure spec), implement a single deterministic entrypoint (seeded RNG, pinned versions), and document the determinism contract in /outputs/eval_loop.md.

Write /outputs/roadmap_v1.md with: domain subtopic lists, explicit completeness criteria (e.g., N textbooks + N surveys + N seminal papers per domain), 20-cycle timebox plan, and a DoD checklist tied to artifacts in /outputs/.

After implementing the skeleton, execute it in CI or locally and store: results.json, figure.png, run_stamp.json (timestamp, git hash, environment), and logs; then link these artifacts from the roadmap and coverage matrix as the first completed deliverables.
